list.item:
Amphetamines have a high potential for abuse; prolonged administration may lead to dependence. (
                                 9
                              )

text.paragraph:
ADDERALL XR, a CNS stimulant, is indicated for the treatment of attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD). (
                              1
                           )

list.item:
Children (ages 6-12):  Efficacy was established in one 3-week outpatient, controlled trial and one analogue classroom, controlled trial in children with ADHD. (
                                 14
                              )

Adolescents (ages 13-17):  Efficacy was established in one 4-week controlled trial in adolescents with ADHD. (
                                 14
                              )

Adults:  Efficacy was established in one 4-week controlled trial in adults with ADHD. (
                                 14
                              )

text.paragraph:
The efficacy of ADDERALL XR in the treatment of ADHD was established on the basis of two controlled trials in children aged 6 to 12, one controlled trial in adolescents aged 13 to 17, and one controlled trial in adults who met DSM-IV® criteria for ADHD [see

                              CLINICAL STUDIES (14)
                           ].

list.item:
Adults:  20 mg once daily in the morning. (
                                 2.4
                              )

Capsules: 5 mg, 10 mg, 15 mg, 20 mg, 25 mg, 30 mg (
                                 3
                              )

Known hypersensitivity or idiosyncrasy to the sympathomimetic amines (e.g., anaphylaxis, angioedema, serious skin rashes) [see

                           ADVERSE REACTIONS (6.2)
                        ]

During or within 14 days following the administration of monoamine oxidase inhibitors (hypertensive crises may result) [see

                           DRUG INTERACTIONS (7.1)
                        ]

Advanced arteriosclerosis (
                                 4
